{"wiki": [{"Resume": "Bill and Melinda Gates own a mansion that overlooks Lake Washington in Medina, Washington. The 66,000-square-foot (6,100 m2) mansion incorporates technology in its design.In 2009, property taxes were reported to be US $1.063 million on a total assessed value of US $147.5 million.\n\n"}, {"Text": "Bill and Melinda Gates own a mansion that overlooks Lake Washington in Medina, Washington. The 66,000-square-foot (6,100 m2) mansion incorporates technology in its design.In 2009, property taxes were reported to be US $1.063 million on a total assessed value of US $147.5 million.\n\n\n== Design and features ==\nThe house was designed collaboratively by Bohlin Cywinski Jackson and Cutler-Anderson Architects of Bainbridge Island, Washington.The mansion is a modern design in the Pacific lodge style, with classic features such as a private library with a dome-shaped roof and oculus. The house features an estate-wide server system, a 60-foot (18 m) swimming pool with an underwater music system, a 2,500-square-foot (230 m2) gym, and a 1,000-square-foot (93 m2) dining room.\n\n\n== In popular culture ==\nThe house was made fun of in Dilbert in January 1997 when the lead character was forced to become a towel boy after his failure to read an end-user license agreement over purchased Microsoft software.Some online news articles call the house Xanadu 2.0, a reference to the motion picture Citizen Kane.\n\n\n== References ==\n\n\n== External links ==\nTax info on the house from the King County GIS website"}, {"URL": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Gates%27s_house"}, {"Links": ["http://www.bcj.com/public/projects/project/12.html", "http://cutler-anderson.com/", "http://www.seattleweekly.com/news/blogs/dailyweekly/2008/05/gates_taxman_cometh.php", "http://geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=Bill_Gates's_house&params=47.62774_N_122.24194_W_region:US-WA_type:landmark", "https://www.businessinsider.com/crazy-facts-about-bill-gates-house-2016-11#its-worth-at-least-127-million-today-1", "https://dilbert.com/strip/1997-01-14", "https://www.forbes.com/2009/03/11/billionaire-homes-expensive-billionaires-2009-lifestyle-real-estate-homes.html#7891dd1a3c43", "https://books.google.com/books?id=klV_BAAAQBAJ&q=bill+gates+house++Bohlin+Cywinski+Jackson+Cutler-Anderson+Architects&pg=PA130", "https://blue.kingcounty.com/Assessor/eRealProperty/Dashboard.aspx?ParcelNbr=9208900079", "https://www.usnews.com/usnews/culture/articles/971201/archive_008409_2.htm", "https://www.usnews.com/usnews/tech/billgate/gates.htm", "https://www.usnews.com/usnews/tech/billgate/room1a.htm", "https://web.archive.org/web/20010428041406/http://www.cutler-anderson.com/", "https://web.archive.org/web/20060104084936/http://www.usnews.com/usnews/tech/billgate/gates.htm", "https://web.archive.org/web/20070928023214/http://www.bcj.com/public/projects/project/12.html", "https://web.archive.org/web/20071011001511/http://www.usnews.com/usnews/tech/billgate/room1a.htm", "https://web.archive.org/web/20130417180124/http://www.seattleweekly.com/news/blogs/dailyweekly/2008/05/gates_taxman_cometh.php", "https://web.archive.org/web/20200917213254/https://books.google.com/books?id=klV_BAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA130&dq=bill+gates+house++Bohlin+Cywinski+Jackson+Cutler-Anderson+Architects&pg=PA130&hl=en#v=onepage&q=bill%20gates%20house%20%20Bohlin%20Cywinski%20Jackson%20Cutler-Anderson%20Architects&f=false", "https://web.archive.org/web/20200917213254/https://dilbert.com/strip/1997-01-14", "https://web.archive.org/web/20200917213254/https://www.forbes.com/2009/03/11/billionaire-homes-expensive-billionaires-2009-lifestyle-real-estate-homes.html#7891dd1a3c43", "https://web.archive.org/web/20200917213311/https://money.usnews.com/money/business-economy/articles/1997/11/23/xanadu-20", "https://www.propertyguru.com.sg/lifestyle/article/4/home-feature-bill-gates-mansion"]}, {"Title": "C"}, {"Categories": ["Articles with short description", "Bill Gates", "Commons category link is on Wikidata", "