ser-output .infobox-3cols-child{margin:auto}.mw-parser-output .infobox .navbar{font-size:100%}body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-header,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-subheader,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-above,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-title,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-image,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-full-data,body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output .infobox-below{text-align:center}</style><table class=\"infobox vcard\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-above fn org\">Bill and Melinda Gates's house</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bill and Melinda Gates&#39; mansion annat\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg/350px-Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"350\" height=\"145\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg/525px-Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg/700px-Residence_of_Bill_Gates.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2856\" data-file-height=\"1184\" /></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align: center\"><a class=\"mw-kartographer-map mw-kartographer-container center\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 200px;\" data-mw=\"interface\" data-style=\"osm-intl\" data-width=\"250\" data-height=\"200\" data-zoom=\"13\" data-lat=\"47.62774\" data-lon=\"-122.24194\" data-overlays=\"[&quot;_3602ef3976fea1eec217791003c9eb7b6e703142&quot;]\" href=\"/wiki/Special:Map/13/47.62774/-122.24194/en\"><img src=\"https://maps.wikimedia.org/img/osm-intl,13,47.62774,-122.24194,250x200.png?lang=en&amp;domain=en.wikipedia.org&amp;title=Bill+Gates%27s+house&amp;groups=_3602ef3976fea1eec217791003c9eb7b6e703142\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"200\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://maps.wikimedia.org/img/osm-intl,13,47.62774,-122.24194,250x200@2x.png?lang=en&amp;domain=en.wikipedia.org&amp;title=Bill+Gates%27s+house&amp;groups=_3602ef3976fea1eec217791003c9eb7b6e703142 2x\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-header\" style=\"background-color:#ededed\">General information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\">Architectural style</th><td class=\"infobox-data category\"><a href=\"/wiki/Pacific_lodge\" title=\"Pacific lodge\">Pacific lodge</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\">Location</th><td class=\"infobox-data label\"><a href=\"/wiki/Medina,_Washington\" title=\"Medina, Washington\">Medina, Washington</a>, United States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a></th><td class=\"infobox-data\"><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r1073938472\">.mw-parser-output .geo-default,.mw-parser-output .geo-dms,.mw-parser-output .geo-dec{display:inline}.mw-parser-output .geo-nondefault,.mw-parser-output .geo-multi-punct{display:none}.mw-parser-output .longitude,.mw-parser-output .latitude{white-space:nowrap}</style><span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=Bill_Gates%27s_house&amp;params=47.62774_N_122.24194_W_region:US-WA_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">47\u00b037\u203240\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">122\u00b014\u203231\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">47.62774\u00b0N 122.24194\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">47.62774; -122.24194</span></span></span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1073938472\"/><span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=Bill_Gates%27s_house&amp;params=47.62774_N_122.24194_W_region:US-WA_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">47\u00b037\u203240\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">122\u00b014\u203231\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">47.62774\u00b0N 122.24194\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">47.62774; -122.24194</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-header\" style=\"background-color:#ededed\">Technical details</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\">Structural system</th><td class=\"infobox-data category\"><a href=\"/wiki/Earth_shelter\" title=\"Earth shelter\">Earth-sheltered home</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Bill_Gates\" title=\"Bill Gates\">Bill</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Melinda_Gates\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Melinda Gates\">Melinda Gates</a> own a <a href=\"/wiki/Mansion\" title=\"Mansion\">mansion</a> that overlooks <a href=\"/wiki/Lake_Washington\" title=\"Lake Washington\">Lake Washington</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Medina,_Washington\" title=\"Medina, Washington\">Medina, Washington</a>. The 66,000-square-foot (6,100&#160;m<sup>2</sup>) mansion incorporates technology in its design.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\"><span title=\"The text near this tag may need clarification or removal of jargon. (May 2021)\">clarification needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In 2009, <a href=\"/wiki/Property_tax\" title=\"Property tax\">property taxes</a> were reported to be US $1.063 million on a total assessed value of US $147.5 million.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Design_and_features\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Design and features</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#In_popular_culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In popular culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Design_and_features\">Design and features</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bill_Gates%27s_house&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Design and features\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The house was designed collaboratively by <a href=\"/wiki/Bohlin_Cywinski_Jackson\" title=\"Bohlin Cywinski Jackson\">Bohlin Cywinski Jackson</a> and Cutler-Anderson Architects of <a href=\"/wiki/Bainbridge_Island,_Washington\" title=\"Bainbridge Island, Washington\">Bainbridge Island</a>, Washington.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cutler_Anderson_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cutler_Anderson-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The mansion is a modern design in the <a href=\"/wiki/Pacific_lodge\" title=\"Pacific lodge\">Pacific lodge</a> style, with classic features such as a private library with a dome-shaped roof and <a href=\"/wiki/Oculus\" title=\"Oculus\">oculus</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The house features an estate-wide server system, a 60-foot (18&#160;m) swimming pool with an underwater music system, a 2,500-square-foot (230&#160;m<sup>2</sup>) gym, and a 1,000-square-foot (93&#160;m<sup>2</sup>) dining room.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_popular_culture\">In popular culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bill_Gates%27s_house&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: In popular culture\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG/220px-Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG/330px-Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG/440px-Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"7360\" data-file-height=\"4912\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_House_2015.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The house in 2015. Many trees block much of the house from view from <a href=\"/wiki/Lake_Washington\" title=\"Lake Washington\">Lake Washington</a>.</div></div></div><p>The house was made fun of in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Dilbert\" title=\"Dilbert\">Dilbert</a></i> in January 1997 when the lead character was forced to become a towel boy after his failure to read an <a href=\"/wiki/End-user_license_agreement\" title=\"End-user license agreement\">end-user license agreement</a> over purchased <a href=\"/wiki/Microsoft\" title=\"Microsoft\">Microsoft</a> software.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Some online news articles call the house Xanadu 2.0, a reference to the motion picture <i><a href=\"/wiki/Citizen_Kane\" title=\"Citizen Kane\">Citizen Kane</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bill_Gates%27s_house&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r1011085734\">.mw-parser-output .reflist{font-size:90%;ma